        <item>
            <title>1.9.0</title>
            <pubDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2026 17:55:01 -0700</pubDate>
            <link>https://nfarina.github.io/ramblr</link>
            <sparkle:fullReleaseNotesLink>https://github.com/nfarina/ramblr/releases/tag/v1.9.0</sparkle:fullReleaseNotesLink>
            <sparkle:version>20</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.9.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>15.2</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description sparkle:format="markdown"><![CDATA[## What's new

- Recent recordings are now kept safely across app updates and relaunches, with a 24-hour default retention window.
- Retranscribe any recent recording, try another model, reveal it in Finder, save it permanently, or delete it immediately.
- Configure audio retention and a storage limit directly from the Ramblr menu.
- Desktop recordings now use compact AAC audio with unique filenames instead of a shared temporary WAV file.
- Failed and interrupted recordings are preserved for recovery, while disposable upload chunks are cleaned up safely.
]]></description>
            <enclosure url="https://github.com/nfarina/ramblr/releases/download/v1.9.0/Ramblr-1.9.0-macos.zip" length="3000626" type="application/octet-stream" sparkle:edSignature="YUkPIwDx/GIcUOI3S51awFCcnD00fAf+FVUZP3bvhrZB8uTMbc/UmZ0iv/n6y+wzq3Z/XUcuFnfhUx16L1SpAA=="/>
        </item>
